[{"id":"VR615324","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a block of mass M sub 0 at rest between two vertical surfaces, where the left and right sides of the block are in contact with the left and right surfaces, respectively. The coefficient of static friction between each vertical surface and the block is mu sub s. A second block of mass lowercase m is placed on top of the first block\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR615324.g02.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M sub 0\"><math alttext=\"M sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> is at rest between two vertical surfaces, each of which exerts a constant normal force <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N sub 0\"><math alttext=\"N sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> on the block. The coefficient of static friction between each vertical surface and the block is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"mu sub s\"><math alttext=\"mu sub s\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>μ</mi><mi>s</mi></msub></math></span></span>. A second block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase m\"><math alttext=\"lowercase m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> is then placed on top of the original block as shown in the figure. What is the largest value <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase m\"><math alttext=\"lowercase m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> can have before the block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M sub 0\"><math alttext=\"M sub 0\" display=\"inline\" o